<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The ki-rin makes three attacks: two with its hooves and one with its horn.</p>

<p><strong><em>Hoof.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +9 to hit, reach 15 ft, one target. Hit: 10 (2d4+5) bludgeoning damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Horn.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +9 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 14 (2d8+5) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong>Legendary Actions</strong></p>

<p>The ki-rin can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creatureâ€™s turn. The ki-rin regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.</p>

<p><strong><em>Detect.</em></strong> The ki-rin makes a Wisdom (Perception) check or a Wisdom (Insight) check.</p>

<p><strong><em>Smite.</em></strong> The ki-rin makes a hoof attack or casts sacred flame.</p>

<p><strong><em>Move.</em></strong> The ki-rin moves up to its half its speed without provoking opportunity attacks.</p>

